<div class="tab-panel" id="tab-learn">

<div class="info">
  <h3>What is CORS?</h3>
  <p>Cross-Origin Resource Sharing (CORS) is a security mechanism that controls which websites can access resources from another domain. When your frontend at <code>app.example.com</code> tries to fetch data from <code>api.another.com</code>, the browser checks CORS headers to decide whether to allow it.</p>
</div>

<div class="info">
  <h3>How it works</h3>
  <p><strong>Simple requests</strong> (GET/POST with standard headers) go directly. The browser checks the response for <code>Access-Control-Allow-Origin</code>.</p>
  <p style="margin-top:8px"><strong>Preflighted requests</strong> (PUT/DELETE, custom headers, non-standard content types) trigger an OPTIONS request first. The server must respond with allowed methods and headers before the actual request proceeds.</p>
  <p style="margin-top:8px"><strong>Credentialed requests</strong> (cookies, auth headers) require <code>Access-Control-Allow-Credentials: true</code> and a specific origin (not <code>*</code>).</p>
</div>

<div class="info">
  <h3>Key CORS Headers</h3>
  <p><code>Access-Control-Allow-Origin</code> — Which origins can access. <code>*</code> = any origin.</p>
  <p style="margin-top:6px"><code>Access-Control-Allow-Methods</code> — Allowed HTTP methods (GET, POST, PUT, etc.).</p>
  <p style="margin-top:6px"><code>Access-Control-Allow-Headers</code> — Allowed custom request headers.</p>
  <p style="margin-top:6px"><code>Access-Control-Max-Age</code> — How long (seconds) to cache preflight results.</p>
  <p style="margin-top:6px"><code>Access-Control-Expose-Headers</code> — Which response headers JS can read.</p>
  <p style="margin-top:6px"><code>Access-Control-Allow-Credentials</code> — Whether cookies/auth can be sent.</p>
</div>

<div class="info">
  <h3>Common CORS Errors</h3>
  <p><strong>"No 'Access-Control-Allow-Origin' header"</strong> — The server doesn't include CORS headers. Fix: add the header server-side.</p>
  <p style="margin-top:6px"><strong>"Wildcard with credentials"</strong> — Can't use <code>*</code> with <code>credentials: include</code>. Fix: echo the specific origin.</p>
  <p style="margin-top:6px"><strong>"Method not allowed"</strong> — The preflight didn't include the method. Fix: add it to <code>Access-Control-Allow-Methods</code>.</p>
  <p style="margin-top:6px"><strong>"Request header not allowed"</strong> — Custom header not in <code>Access-Control-Allow-Headers</code>. Fix: add it.</p>
</div>

<div class="info">
  <h3>Server-Side Fix Examples</h3>
  <p><strong>Express.js:</strong></p>
  <p><code>app.use(cors({ origin: 'https://myapp.com', credentials: true }))</code></p>
  <p style="margin-top:8px"><strong>Nginx:</strong></p>
  <p><code>add_header Access-Control-Allow-Origin "https://myapp.com";</code></p>
  <p style="margin-top:8px"><strong>Apache (.htaccess):</strong></p>
  <p><code>Header set Access-Control-Allow-Origin "https://myapp.com"</code></p>
</div>

</div>
